HEADWORD: Petrous
<hw>Pe"trous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>petrosus</ets>, fr. <ets>petra</ets> a stone.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Like stone; hard; stony; rocky; <as>as, the <ex>petrous</ex> part
of the temporal bone</as>.</def> <rj><au>Hooper.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Same as
